===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[momentum#Latin|momentum]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'məʊmənt/}}
*{{audio|en-us-moment.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[brief]], unspecified amount of [[time]]
# [[weight]] or [[importance]]
#:*'''1904''': the document in question is of such immense importance that its publication might very easily – I might almost say probably – lead to European complications of the utmost '''moment'''. — Arthur Conan Doyle, ‘The Adventure of the Second Stain’ (Norton 2005, p.1192)
# 90 seconds (arch)
# {{physics}} The [[magnitude]] of [[force]] applied to a [[rotational]] [[system]] at a [[distance]] from the [[axis]] of [[rotation]].  Also called moment of force.  

